6.  Anti-Corruption: Satota  Engineering  strictly  prohibits  any  form  of  bribery,  corruption,  or 
unethical payments. Employees must adhere to  anti-corruption laws  and  policies in all business 
interactions. 
7. Health and Safety: Ensuring a safe and healthy work environment is paramount. Employees 
are expected to comply with safety protocols, report hazards promptly, and actively participate in 
maintaining a safe workplace. 
8.   Environmental   Responsibility: Satota   Engineering   is   committed   to   environmental 
sustainability.  Employees  should  take  measures  to  minimize  the  company's  environmental 
footprint and adhere to relevant environmental regulations. 
9. Diversity and inclusion: Satota Engineering values diversity and inclusion. Discrimination or 
harassment  based  on  race,  gender,  age,  religion,  or  any  other  protected  characteristic  is  strictly 
prohibited, fostering an inclusive workplace for all. 
10.  Fair  Employment  Practices: All  employment  decisions  should  be  based  on  merit  and 
qualifications.  Satota  Engineering  maintains  a  fair  and  unbiased  approach  to  hiring,  promotion, 
compensation, and termination. 
11. Reporting Violations: Satota Engineering encourages a culture of transparency and integrity. 
Employees are urged to report any breaches of the code of conduct or suspected unethical behavior 
through established channels without fear of retaliation. 
12. Use of Company Resources: Company resources, including equipment, facilities, and time, 
are  to  be  used  solely  for  business  purposes.  Personal  or  unauthorized  use  of  these  resources  is 
prohibited. 
13.  Accuracy  of  Records  and  Reporting: Maintaining  accurate  and  transparent  records  is 
essential. Employees must ensure that all business records and reports are truthful, complete, and 
free from any misrepresentation. 
14.  Professionalism: Employees  are  ambassadors  of  Satota  Engineering.  Professional  and 
respectful conduct is expected in all interactions, reflecting positively on the company's reputation. 

