15. Supplier and Partner Relationships: Satota Engineering fosters fair and ethical relationships 
with  suppliers,  partners,  and  stakeholders.  Upholding  honesty,  integrity,  and  mutual  respect  in 
these relationships is essential. 
16.  Gifts  and  Entertainment: Any  gifts,  entertainment,  or  hospitality  offered  or  received  by 
employees should comply with company gifting policies and legal guidelines. These should not 
influence or compromise business decisions. 
17.  Social  Responsibility: Satota  Engineering  encourages  employees  to  engage  positively  with 
the  communities  in  which  it  operates.  This  could  involve  volunteering,  supporting  charitable 
initiatives, or contributing to community development. 
18.  Training  and  Awareness: Satota  Engineering  provides  training  and  resources  to  ensure 
employees  fully  understand  and  adhere  to  the  code  of  conduct.  Regular  training  sessions  keep 
everyone up-to-date on ethical standards and best practices. 
19. Continuous Improvement: Satota Engineering commits to regularly reviewing and updating 
its  code  of  conduct  to  stay  abreast  of  evolving  ethical  standards  and  best  practices,  ensuring 
relevance and effectiveness. 
20.  Acknowledgment: By  joining  Satota  Engineering,  employees,  contractors,  interns,  and 
volunteers acknowledge  their understanding of and agreement to abide by this code of business 
conduct, upholding the company's values and standards. 
 
 
    
 
 
 
 
 
